icus following injury in salt water (1986) Journal of Clinical Microbiology, 23 (2), pp. 373-374; Patterson, T.F., Bell, S.R., Bia, F.J., Vibrio alginolyticus cellulitis following coral injury (1988) Yale Journal of Biology and Medicine, 61 (6), pp. 507-512; Pien, F., Lee, K., Higa, H., Vibrio alginolyticus infections in Hawaii (1977) Journal of Clinical Microbiology, 5 (6), pp. 670-672; Hansen, W., Crokaert, F., Yourassowsky, E., Two strains of Vibrio species with unusual biochemical features isolated from ear tracts (1979) Journal of Clinical Microbiology, 9 (1), pp. 152-153; Spark, R.P., Fried, M.L., Perry, C., Watkins, C., Vibrio alginolyticus wound infection: Case report and review (1979) Annals of Clinical and Laboratory Science, 9 (2), pp. 133-138; Von Graevenitz, A., Carrington, G.O., Halophilic vibrios from extraintestinal lesions in man (1973) Infection, 1 (1), pp. 54-58; Morris Jr., J.G., Black, R.E., Cholera and other vibrioses in the United States (1985) New England Journal of Medicine, 312 (6), pp. 343-350; Rubin, S.J., Tilton, R.C., Isolation of Vibrio alginolyticus from wound infections (1975) J Clin Microbiol., 2 (6), pp. 556-558; McSweeney, R.J., Forgan Smith, W.R., Wound infections in Australia from halophilic vibrios (1977) Medical Journal of Australia, 1 (24), pp. 896-897; English, V.L., Lindberg, R.B., Isolation of Vibrio alginolyticus from wounds and blood of a burn patient (1977) Am J Med Technol, 43 (10), pp. 989-993; Ryan, W.J., Marine vibrios associated with superficial septic lesions (1976) J Clin Pathol, 29 (11), pp. 1014-1015; Prociv, P., Vibrio alginolyticus in western Australia (1978) Medical Journal of Australia, 2 (7), p. 296; Bonner, J.R., Coker, A.S., Berryman, C.R., Pollock, H.M., Spectrum of vibrio infections in a Gulf Coast community (1983) Ann Intern Med, 99 (4), pp. 464-469; Pezzlo, M., Valter, P.J., Burns, M.J., Wound infection associated with Vibrio alginolyticus (1979) American Journal of Clinical Pathology, 71 (4), pp. 47